The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Sen post
                                                                                                                     4                                                                                      Sen post
                            
	Calcutta, March 17: Bengals longest serving industry secretary, Sabyasachi Sen, has been made an additional chief secretary and appointed commissioner-general of land and land reforms.        
	He (Sen) will continue to look after the industries department till his successor joins, said chief secretary Asok Mohan Chakrabarti.        
	Sen, due to retire next year, has been the industries secretary for more than seven years during which period the farm-versus-factory debate made its debut in Bengal politics.         
	Sen was the main negotiator on behalf of the government in all projects  the Nano in Singur to the proposed chemical hub in Nayachar.                                                                                                                                                             
